<subSubSection id="D83563FE7A6702A85652172618B0F5A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="4CBC1507987FA9DF26DF8D776D45D17A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06895E35ECED10A45FCE48C12A283FB4" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="C034D1E74F86D674AE51ED68C86E3942" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Body</emphasis>
: small, length approximately 2 to 2.5 mm, ovoid, convex but slightly flattened dorso-ventrally, dorsally body surface completely obscured with appressed or recumbent setae, scale-like especially on head and elytra.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E1534C7CE2CE984BB4D86405767D9350" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="76D7507C0FD0F6BD9948C6D6D9304D29" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4CDE3238E89163BA68C006E458EAC7A8" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Head, frontal view B labrum, dorsal view C mandible, ventral view D maxilla, ventral view E labium, dorsal view F mentum, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A), 0.1 mm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411666" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">4A</figureCitation>
): Eyes not visible dorsally, small, ovoid, slightly rounded ommatidial surface facing slightly upwards; vertex very slightly convex, antennal fossae generally indistinct, smoothly rounded edges, but more distinct dorsally and laterally absent; a large distinct pocket extending laterally from fossa through to gena between eye and lateral edge of clypeus; antennae short in length, no longer than the maximum width of the pronotum, 11 antennomeres, 4-10 relatively stout, only slightly longer than wide, second antennomere inserted off center of scape near lateral edge; interantennal space between antennal insertions wide, width approximately the same as length of scape, flat with no carina between antennal fossae; clypeus triangular, maximal width ≈ 4/5 width of head measured adjacent to pronotum, labrum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="884FE8C2AC1810863BC877B534DF81F1" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Head, frontal view B labrum, dorsal view C mandible, ventral view D maxilla, ventral view E labium, dorsal view F mentum, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A), 0.1 mm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411666" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">4B</figureCitation>
) ca. 1/3 width of clypeus, anterior edge very slightly emarginated in middle; mandible apex acutely pointed, medial tooth present (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3AB4D943077C26A5650E865A78AA1D16" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Head, frontal view B labrum, dorsal view C mandible, ventral view D maxilla, ventral view E labium, dorsal view F mentum, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A), 0.1 mm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411666" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">4C</figureCitation>
); maxillary and labial palps with four and three palpomeres respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="80889EC403014BEE4B7BBC86D6505E4F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Head, frontal view B labrum, dorsal view C mandible, ventral view D maxilla, ventral view E labium, dorsal view F mentum, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A), 0.1 mm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411666" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">4D, E</figureCitation>
); mentum triangular, with small triangular cavity at middle (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BEE5D4828CA8145151C3A18182E687CA" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Head, frontal view B labrum, dorsal view C mandible, ventral view D maxilla, ventral view E labium, dorsal view F mentum, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A), 0.1 mm (B-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411666" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="187A099A6794B0C83F1DAD9C5878AC28" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="9B728D948E1A81A99FD836362260223E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Pronotum</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2644CA41A29B5329AF16DBA2537DE7CA" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Elytra, dorsal view B prothorax, frontal view, C aedeagus, dorsal view D meso- and metaventrites and abdominal ventrites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D), 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411665" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">3B</figureCitation>
): Strongly transverse with five depressions adjacent to the posterior margin, one large median and two smaller laterally on each side (Figs 
<figureCitation id="7F2595728B5CDF85C5C9D3F717C8D3A4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Cordielytrum peruvianum sp. nov. A Dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C lateral view D frontal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411663" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DF57937C0B6124A27C76B5D98DA48DD7" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C lateral view D frontal view. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411664" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">2A</figureCitation>
); elongate erect setae on lateral edge extending laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B1B7C40423E823E5A942E17F41ABC926" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="21953317D98B223BE26CA65651BE5EA2" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Elytra</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="03653911AC746BBDD035DA608AC37E7C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Elytra, dorsal view B prothorax, frontal view, C aedeagus, dorsal view D meso- and metaventrites and abdominal ventrites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D), 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411665" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">3A</figureCitation>
): Heart-shaped, convex, fused along suture; longitudinal carinae at least at base and sometimes visible the entire length of each elytron, short suberect setae on carinae; relatively elongate setae on humeral area that extend laterally and curve posteriorly near their apex; 2-3 irregular fine puncture rows between each carina.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="23D17AFCE3FA7DE9FC235C947906FA23" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="BBF2B98FE5D41B201D08F84D6D59448C" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2221347570BB4757DC4A6CB3C38A901F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Elytra, dorsal view B prothorax, frontal view, C aedeagus, dorsal view D meso- and metaventrites and abdominal ventrites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D), 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411665" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">3D</figureCitation>
): Broader than long; prosternal process narrow anteriorly, widening posteriorly, teardrop- shaped, extending posteriorly to same distance as procoxae do posteriorly, extending slightly into mesoventrite; visible part of mesoventrite heart-shaped with a truncate tip posteriorly, between coxae slightly longer than wide, slightly shorter than length of metaventrite at middle; posterior margin of metaventrite broadly emarginated; mesoventral-mesepisternal and metaventral-metepisternal sutures both visible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D67E5E001B5860BE712F2389562EEC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="1A3FD7A2785F9C6857AC9872D1914370" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Abdominal ventrites</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="07610CD5ABBB61C6143FE0A940B64CFC" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Elytra, dorsal view B prothorax, frontal view, C aedeagus, dorsal view D meso- and metaventrites and abdominal ventrites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D), 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411665" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">3D</figureCitation>
): Ventrites broad, ca. 2/3 total width of body measured at/opposite ventrite base, all sutures visible, first three ventrites connate, length at middle compared to laterally slightly shorter except fifth where longest at middle; first and second approximately equal in length, third slightly shorter, fourth distinctly shortest, fifth distinctly longest.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64F3E6876B181439C5C3057A699BD493" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="95778432EB0407E88782E18EBD3DE858" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Legs</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="71152C6C7BF29630615945283471FF8A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Elytra, dorsal view B prothorax, frontal view, C aedeagus, dorsal view D meso- and metaventrites and abdominal ventrites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D), 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411665" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">3B, D</figureCitation>
): moderate in length, femora widest near middle; tibia gradually expanded toward apex, pro- and mesotibiae similar in length to their respective femora, metatibiae distinctly longer; tarsomeres 2-4 ca. as wide as long, 1st and 5th ca. equal in length; procoxae and mesocoxae approximately rounded, procoxae slightly smaller in diameter than mesocoxae, metacoxae transverse, fused with metaventrite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C93E07BF0016728C59080067FA5F43EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="C1F0C99421DF920C9005FEEFDFBBD5E5" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7D0F1B88B6B2385E6305ED4C89D0656D" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cordielytrum pulchrum sp. nov. A Elytra, dorsal view B prothorax, frontal view, C aedeagus, dorsal view D meso- and metaventrites and abdominal ventrites. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, D), 0.1 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.934.38670.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/411665" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">3C</figureCitation>
): relatively simple; parameres and median lobe relatively stout, parameres lacking setal clumps or other modifications.
</paragraph>
