<subSubSection id="80F5780DC29CC59172B3B3BEA16BAB58" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="93A8AA3DC7329C00F98FBA15031F479F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="974334928175B90CBFBC4103E7B7CD2E" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Currently no information on the ecology is known with the exception of the northernmost species that was collected via traps baited with a local corn beer known as chicha: this fluid may have been attractive as a food and/or moisture source. Based on recent collections and current rearing experiments (Philips and Whorrall, unpublished), larvae feed on cat dung and likely any other type in their vicinity, such as that from other mammals, birds, or lizards.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
